Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE RESOLUTION ____
MR. PRESIDENT:
I offer the following resolution and move its adoption:
1 A SENATE RESOLUTION honoring the Guerin Catholic
2 High School Golden Gears FIRST Robotics team.
3 Whereas, The Guerin Catholic Golden Gears FIRST
4 Robotics team is composed of students who aim to learn,
5 create, and compete in the exciting world of robotics;
6 Whereas, As a member of the FIRST Indiana Robotics
7 district, the Golden Gears ranked 17th out of 71 teams in their
8 first competition season, also racking up accolades such as the
9 Rookie All-Star Award and the Quality Award throughout the
10 competition year;
11 Whereas, Through rigorous training and hands-on
12 workshops, the Golden Gears prepare for competitions with
13 their team of maturing engineers, programmers, designers, and
14 strategists;
15 Whereas, The Golden Gears offer mentorship, training, and
16 opportunities for students to grow personally and
17 professionally; and
18 Whereas, Students at Guerin Catholic High School are
2026 RR 3518/DI JR

2
1 able to design, build, and program robots in a collaborative
2 learning environment, encouraging creativity and critical
3 thinking, all while the Golden Gears celebrate successes, learn
4 from failures, and continuously strive to improve: Therefore,
5 Be it resolved by the Senate of the
6 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
7 SECTION 1. That the Indiana Senate honors the Guerin
8 Catholic High School Golden Gears FIRST Robotics team.
9 SECTION 2. The Secretary of the Senate is hereby directed
10 to transmit copies of this Resolution to the Guerin Catholic
11 High School Golden Gears FIRST Robotics team.
